The paper discusses the implementation of a Deep Recurrent Neural Network Language Model on a Xilinx FPGA, which falls under the category of machine learning and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of AXI Stream interface and hardware acceleration, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions the application of the model in natural language processing, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.EM (Emerging Technologies).
